cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is about reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of control variate technique and function approximation in the proposed algorithm suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the convergence rate of the algorithm, which is related to optimization, making "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of the algorithm in control systems and robotics, as mentioned in the introduction, suggests that it could also belong to "cs.SY" (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the variance reduction technique, which is a common challenge in reinforcement learning, making "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of tabular methods and the comparison with other TD learning algorithms suggests that it could also belong to "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms).
